                                           \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/copy-of-169-5.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/copy-of-169-5.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"2160\" height=\"1215\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Person using 8BitDo Ultimate 2C\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/copy-of-169-5.png\" src=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/copy-of-169-5.png\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                    \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n                                    \u003cp\u003eSource:Â 8BitDo\u003c/p\u003e\n                        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhen it comes to compatibility, you\u0026#39;re getting a controller that can work with most Android devices and also Windows PCs as well. It can work using Bluetooth, or you can also use the included 2.4Ghz connector if your device permits it. The latter is going to provide a better connection, with up to 1000Hz polling rate, so we recommend going with that option if you can.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eThe controller looks and feels good, offering a comfortable fit that houses the usual things you\u0026#39;ll find on a controller, like a D-pad, buttons, triggers, and shoulder buttons. But 8BitDo takes things a step further, utilizing hall effect sticks and triggers to ensure you get the best experience that will last a long time.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eThe controller even features extra bumpers on the rear that can be configured using the included software, which is great if you\u0026#39;re looking for some customization. Overall, not a bad controller that\u0026#39;s both robust in features but also highly affordable. Just be sure to grab it while it\u0026#39;s still on sale.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\n    \n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                                            \n\n\n\n\n        \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n            \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
